workflow.properties.overview.descriptionText:
Lists all workflows defined for the instance.

Click Edit to manage a workflow.
To enable or disable a workflow schedule, select the workflow and click Enable or Disable respectively.
Select a workflow and click Run (queue and start) to manually run a workflow.

Note: Running a workflow directly is not supported. Instead it is possible to put the workflow to the execution queue. Depending on the current running workflows it can take a time to run the workflow.

workflow.properties.workflow.components.title: Components - Drag & drop to change the order of the components
workflow.properties.workflow.descriptionText:
Configuration of the workflow and its components - Edit main information about frequency, run times, enablement, notifications and relate components to this workflow.
Note: Changing the component-execution-order is done by dragging and dropping the component by its header to the needed position.

The selectable site IDs are managed in the organization preference Workflow Framwork->siteIds.

Note: Changing a current running workflow has no effect on the running workflow.
Note: Point of times which are in the past (referencing the last change of the workflow) will not be respected when executing the workflow.
Note: All dates and times are shown in the instance time zone.

forms_en.properties.contactus.referenceproduct.tooltiptext:
The product reference is on the device. The latter is preceded by a “Mod.” or “REF.:” Some examples:
  • On the handle of your hair dryer, beginning with the letter D, or the number 6 or 5
  • Between the two plates of your straightener, on the handle side, starting with the letters ST
  • On the handle of your airbrush, beginning with the letters AS, or the number 6 or 2
  • On the handle of your Curl Secret or your curling iron, beginning with the letter C
  • On the body of your epilator, or when removing the head from the latter, beginning with the letter G
  • On the body of your trimmer, beginning with the letter E or T
